  "comment": "Battery powered Par fixture with 9 x 6W Quad-colour RGBA LEDs.  Includes D-Fi.  \nNotes:\n1. The sound mode runs it's own program and is not reliant on other settings (apart from dimmer).  You can adjust the sensitivity.\n2. Auto programs take priority over colour macros\n3. The foreground (FG) and background (BG) colours operate in auto programs 5-9.  These programs alternate between the two colors you set.  You can change the intensity the two colours separately.  \n4. I've tested it with the fixture and in grandMA3 3D view.  The auto programs and macros don't display in 3D as these are commands sent to the fixture's internal processor, not emitter values.   \n\nRevisions\nV1.001 - Corrected 3D view issue\nV1.002 - Further improvements for rendering in 3D on lighting software\nV1.003 - Set Dimmer speed to Fastest by default",
